CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 5, 1963, pg. 1, reads: "ON DUTY - Pickets of the United Negro Protest Committee wind their way up Braddock Ave. past the headquarters of Mine Safety Appliances. The marchers walked in front of the plant, on Tuesday, and then resumed their picketing at 1 P.M. on Wednesday (today). - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Picketers, possibly including Cathy Milton second from right and Rev. J. A. Williams wearing dark tie, carrying NAACP protest signs marching outside United Mine Safety Appliance Company, Braddock Avenue, Homewood
